# Paper Trail Preference

Keep intermediate artifacts (logs, raw outputs, event streams, build diagnostics) when they contain useful information and storage cost is trivial. Delete only when the artifact is large and low-value, or fully redundant with something already retained.

If an artifact must be deleted (size, sensitivity, ephemeral filesystem), extract the useful information into a retained file first.

**Default: keep.** The burden of proof is on deletion, not retention.
